<br>
Like Brettsc said, it depends on how quick you can prepare for the next killing of him.<br>
<br>
With the Guardian up still, the Lord repops constantly.  The Guardian will repop as well if there are any other smaller birds still alive &quot;and&quot; there is no aggro on them.  This is important.  We had the last little bird in camp and mezzed, waiting for the guardian to repop before killing him.  Guardian wouldn't repop.  We had to unaggro the little bird to get him to respawn.  Everyone camped out and came right back.  Guardian popped then.  Remember that if the same thing happens to you, as the Guardian is unmezzable, and you're forced to kill him if he comes into camp (or get wiped if you just let him run around wacking people).  If he's not popping, and there are still other small birds alive, have everyone camp out and come back before killing that last little bird.<br>
<br>
I don't really remember how long it took us.  Hours.  Most of the afternoon.  What slowed us down more than ourselves getting ready though was Sirran the Lunatic.  We didn't really plan out the positioning, and often had to clear him from camp (monk would try to pull him away and feign, but ended up dead most of the time doing so... he's a fast little bugger).  The island was far smaller than we expected, so instead of risking aggroing the guardian while moving camp around constantly, we just moved Sirran.  We didn't want to take any chances.  Aggroing the guardian would have meant purposeful wipeout while we camped a cleric, since the Lord farming would end if we were to kill the guardian.<br>
<br>
Sirran won't pop on the Lords death if he's already up somewhere else.  So we would get 3 to 4 Lords down before Sirran would have to be moved again (despawned where he was, and respawned where we killed the next Lord).  About a 20 minute despawn on Sirran.<br>
<br>
The Lord popped instantly again every time we killed him.  Whether his body was laying on the ground still or not, there was always a new Lord up the second the one we were killing dropped.<br>
<br>
You can see him holding the blade as well.  So you'll know when he's going to drop it or not. <p>--Hagus Bruichladdich<BR>
