<br>
The island consists of 3 Vanquishers, each of whom have 2 assigned 'buddies'. The pairing is not random, and are set up as: Vanquisher/Arbiter/Banisher, Vanquisher/Caller/Walker, Vanquisher/Expulser/Revolter.<br>
<br>
If you kill any of the 'buddies' before you kill their Vanquisher, they'll respawn instantly once the Vanquisher is unaggro. You must kill the Vanquisher if you want the triads to die.<br>
<br>
Vanquishers are 57 or 58, and have about 23k hp and hit for 250 and enrage, as well as the standard blind/lightning/root/and AE that all the Spirocs do.<br>
The 'Buddies' are 52 or 53, and have 23k and hit for 200s, but don't enrage.<br>
<br>
The Guardian is 60, has 23k hp, and hits for 250. Resists most of the stuff other than lures unless you debuff the hell out of him. He will respawn instantly unless all three of the Vanquishers are dead or aggro.<br>
<br>
The lord is over 60, hits for 350, has 32k hp. Does all the standard Spiroc stuff as well as a really annoying stun proc and the bullshit DT. He'll repop instantly unless the Guardian is dead or aggro. You don't have to loot the corpses like someone said, I have some screenshots of 3 dead lords in a stack with us fighting the 4th =P<br>
<br>
Narris doesn't always spawn after each kill, but when he does you'll have to move the camp (pain in the ass) or just send a ranger or someone else with a long-range bow/arrows to stick the froggy king in the arse and move him away from camp. Paladins are a good choice, since they're more useful dead.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, it's fairly obvious that any mob on the island can be farmed infinitely. You shouldn't really have problems getting the quest pieces you need from here.<br>
<br>
Good luck, the hardest part of this plane is staying awake. Well, that and actually convincing enough people to come along to soak DTs for you. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=98708">Vargr</a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=93696">Xiff</a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=260982">Malsheen</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wychway>Wychway</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 12:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=490.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: THE GUARDIAN</span><hr size=1> Gnomes are superior DT sponges for the Lord pull. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91801">Wychway Darkmink</a><BR>Inky Warlord, Bristlebane<BR><br>Facts:<br>1. Minks are mammals.<br> 
